content.description: The Telephone Booth ascends the far right side of the northwest face of Spire Rock. Sit start using the "smile" hold and lock into a drop knee stem, pull up to the two slopers and go straight up through the bulge to the top. Reaching straight through from the slopers to the "dish" above the bulge is V4. Using holds to the left make it V3. The base of this problem can be underwater when the tide or river is high.
content.location: Walk around spire rock to the northwest face.

content.description: The East Face Right follows crimps and side pulls up the highest part of the east face of Spire rock. This one is high enough to make it thrilling, especially when the sand is low. The hardest part is over by the time you reach the half way point but the top out will still keep your attention. Classic!
content.protection: Sand or pad. Watch the landing, it is a good idea to have a spotter to the right if the sand is washed out.
content.location: 100 feet west of the parking lot.

content.description: The East Face Left climbs positive holds along the left edge of this face. Always in the shade and often out of the wind, this and and the East Face Right are two of the most climbed problems at Moonstone. Great rock and classic moves. The east face also has a many eliminates and variations.
content.location: 100 feet west of the parking area.
